		<td><b>Re: Video games on the other side of the iron curtain</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm only guessing, but considering Russia only seems to know about the Dendy (if adverts from the time are anything to go by), they probably never got the official PAL Famicom. I don't know about any other consoles, but it's hard to believe that they had <em>nothing</em> until recently. I guess it comes down to figuring out when Russian started appearing on language select menus for PAL games.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


